1
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
"Double Helix"

2
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:16,800
(Episode 6: This is probably our fondest memory together.)

3
00:01:17,319 --> 00:01:18,400
Who is it?

4
00:01:18,719 --> 00:01:19,840
What's going on?

5
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:21,760
What's that noise?

6
00:01:21,761 --> 00:01:22,881
Is your girlfriend in there?

7
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:24,040
What?

8
00:01:25,359 --> 00:01:26,840
Well, well, Cheng Yichen.

9
00:01:27,719 --> 00:01:28,959
Hiding a secret lover, are we?

10
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Who is it?

11
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:36,400
Hello.

12
00:01:37,599 --> 00:01:38,599
Mr. Lu.

13
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,079
Um...

14
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,999
Don't get the wrong idea.

15
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:44,840
Here's what happened.

16
00:01:44,841 --> 00:01:46,319
The lock on Mr. Lu's door is broken.

17
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,840
So he couldn't get in.

18
00:01:47,841 --> 00:01:48,958
He's just crashing here for the night.

19
00:01:48,959 --> 00:01:49,799
You know...

20
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:50,920
We're old classmates.

21
00:01:54,879 --> 00:01:56,120
Come on in.

22
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,760
Old classmates.

23
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:16,680
I'm hungry.

24
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:19,680
I'll go make some food then.

25
00:02:57,599 --> 00:02:58,599
Dinner's ready.

26
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:07,599
Yichen.

27
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,879
Are you and Mr. Lu... you know... involved?

28
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,560
Are you okay?

29
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,999
Xiao Chen, what's wrong?

30
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,256
It's nothing, it's nothing. Yichen.

31
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,280
I'm fine.

32
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,159
You burned yourself.

33
00:03:17,159 --> 00:03:18,159
I'm fine.

34
00:03:18,319 --> 00:03:19,319
Here.

35
00:03:20,879 --> 00:03:21,879
Are you crazy?

36
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,439
Don't. There are people here.

37
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,560
People are here.

38
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,240
I don't know.

39
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:31,080
Does it hurt a lot?

40
00:03:34,639 --> 00:03:35,759
The water's a bit cold.

41
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,560
Will it hurt?

42
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:48,919
It's fine.

43
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,399
It's just a small burn.

44
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,600
Can you get me the toothpaste?

45
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:06,440
How could you be so careless?

46
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:09,038
I told you, I'm fine.

47
00:04:09,039 --> 00:04:10,520
What if they figure it out?

48
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,120
You got hurt right in front of me.

49
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,439
Can't I even be a little worried?

50
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,000
When I was in the States,

51
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:50,759
I knew this couple.

52
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,079
One of them died in a car accident.

53
00:04:56,279 --> 00:04:58,279
At the funeral, the one who was left...

54
00:04:58,600 --> 00:05:00,480
didn't even dare to cry out loud.

55
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,560
He was so afraid his parents
would find out about them.

56
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:08,559
I don't want to live like that,
compromising everything.

57
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,039
I want the whole world to know...

58
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:11,079
that I'm with you.

59
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,000
What about you?

60
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,040
I won't hide it from you anymore.

61
00:06:00,639 --> 00:06:01,639
Xiao Chen and I...

62
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,680
are a couple.

63
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,199
We got together when we were 18.

64
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,160
And from now on,

65
00:06:12,199 --> 00:06:13,319
we'll never be apart again.

66
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,240
If he's willing,

67
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,880
we'll be together for
the rest of our lives.

68
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:24,240
Although I have no obligation...

69
00:06:24,241 --> 00:06:25,441
to explain anything to you,

70
00:06:26,319 --> 00:06:27,959
you're Xiao Chen's friends.

71
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,400
I hope that after knowing this,

72
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,800
you can still be good friends with him.

73
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:39,719
But if I find out...

74
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:42,000
that anyone is spreading
rumors to hurt him,

75
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:46,279
I will be sure to return the favor.

76
00:06:46,959 --> 00:06:48,079
Tenfold.

77
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,160
Do you want to stay for dinner?

78
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:58,240
See? I told you my intuition was right.

79
00:06:58,319 --> 00:06:59,319
Let's eat, let's eat.

80
00:07:00,839 --> 00:07:01,839
Come on.

81
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,920
Here, Mr. Lu.

82
00:07:04,519 --> 00:07:06,040
Since we're not at the office,

83
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:07,759
I don't have to call you Mr. Lu.

84
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,000
Lu Feng.

85
00:07:09,519 --> 00:07:10,519
Let's have a drink.

86
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:22,600
When you two get married,

87
00:07:22,601 --> 00:07:24,241
don't forget to invite us to the wedding.

88
00:07:25,439 --> 00:07:26,495
You'll cover our flights
and hotel, right, boss?

89
00:07:26,519 --> 00:07:27,560
No problem.

90
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:32,079
To be honest,

91
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,000
I don't really get it.

92
00:07:34,319 --> 00:07:35,319
But...

93
00:07:35,519 --> 00:07:36,920
you two seem...

94
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:38,360
good together.

95
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,279
If Yichen is happy,

96
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,200
then that's all that matters.

97
00:07:45,839 --> 00:07:46,839
Thank you.

98
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,199
Those two words...

99
00:07:53,199 --> 00:07:55,279
were spoken with a
sincerity that broke my heart.

100
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:58,319
He knew our perseverance
had nothing to lean on.

101
00:07:59,759 --> 00:08:01,639
The only thing we were
sure of was our love.

102
00:08:03,279 --> 00:08:04,800
But in this day and age,

103
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:08,240
even being in love has
become a lonely battle.

104
00:08:09,839 --> 00:08:10,839
Lu Feng...

105
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:14,680
is the strongest warrior in this war.

106
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:22,920
Mr. Lu.

107
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,680
What are you doing?

108
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,800
I'm hungry.

109
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:54,399
Lu Feng.

110
00:08:54,639 --> 00:08:55,799
Don't be shy.

111
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Hold on tighter.

112
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:58,159
There are people around.

113
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,399
There's no one here.

114
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:01,759
What era are we living in?

115
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,519
Can't two guys ride a bike together?

116
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,400
It's not right, out here on the main road.

117
00:09:06,559 --> 00:09:07,559
Look at them.

118
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:08,480
They're so open about it.

119
00:09:08,639 --> 00:09:10,080
Well, they're them.

120
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:14,799
Why do they look so familiar from behind?

121
00:09:15,519 --> 00:09:16,519
Yi-chen.

122
00:09:17,759 --> 00:09:18,759
Bro.

123
00:09:19,399 --> 00:09:20,399
Surprise.

124
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,519
Out here in public,

125
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:22,760
you two should be more careful.

126
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,880
What are you guys doing here?

127
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:26,519
I came...

128
00:09:26,519 --> 00:09:27,519
because I have some good news.

129
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,760
I wanted to tell you in person.

130
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,399
And since tomorrow's the weekend,

131
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:31,879
I thought I'd come hang out.

132
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:32,840
What's the good news?

133
00:09:33,039 --> 00:09:35,039
I'm finally starting my own band.

134
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,360
Really?

135
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:37,519
I'm staying here tonight.

136
00:09:37,519 --> 00:09:38,080
But, bro,

137
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,535
could you sound any less excited?

138
00:09:39,559 --> 00:09:40,279
I'm not being unenthusiastic.

139
00:09:40,279 --> 00:09:41,000
I'm being sincere.

140
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,240
Very unenthusiastic.

141
00:09:43,679 --> 00:09:45,039
The show is next month.

142
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:46,120
At his bar.

143
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,200
You have to come.

144
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:48,279
Okay.

145
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:50,040
Look at you two, holding hands already.

146
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:56,679
Just for one night.

147
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:58,960
One night.

148
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:01,960
Yi-chen.

149
00:10:03,279 --> 00:10:04,439
The guest room is over there.

150
00:10:06,679 --> 00:10:07,320
I don't care.

151
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:08,936
I don't want to sleep in the guest room.

152
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,399
I want to sleep with my brother.

153
00:10:10,919 --> 00:10:12,039
How old are you?

154
00:10:12,639 --> 00:10:13,639
None of your business.

155
00:10:14,519 --> 00:10:15,519
How about...

156
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,840
he sleeps with me tonight?

157
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:20,518
There are only two rooms here.

158
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:21,558
If you sleep with him,

159
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:22,839
am I supposed to sleep with him?

160
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:24,000
That won't be necessary.

161
00:10:24,001 --> 00:10:25,360
I can sleep on the couch.

162
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:27,919
Well...

163
00:10:29,559 --> 00:10:30,559
Okay, then.

164
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,320
No way.

165
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,360
Come here.

166
00:10:35,399 --> 00:10:36,440
You're so rich.

167
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:38,879
You can go back to your big house.

168
00:10:41,519 --> 00:10:42,519
Good night.

169
00:10:50,679 --> 00:10:53,399
Bro, it's been so long
since I've slept with you.

170
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:55,558
How are you guys?

171
00:10:55,559 --> 00:10:56,559
Is he treating you well?

172
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,039
He wouldn't dare not to.

173
00:10:58,600 --> 00:10:59,600
I'm not just saying this,

174
00:11:00,039 --> 00:11:01,199
but don't bully him too much.

175
00:11:01,399 --> 00:11:02,240
Hey,

176
00:11:02,241 --> 00:11:03,639
who's bullying who?

177
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:04,759
Don't be fooled by him.

178
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,360
He seems good-tempered on the surface,

179
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,558
but he's secretly mischievous.

180
00:11:07,559 --> 00:11:08,480
You just don't see it.

181
00:11:08,481 --> 00:11:09,639
You only ever praise him.

182
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,200
Alright, alright.

183
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,360
As long as you're happy.

184
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,440
Time for bed.

185
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,480
Don't just talk about me.

186
00:11:17,799 --> 00:11:19,919
So you two made up?

187
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:27,000
Guess I can't keep you to myself anymore.

188
00:11:30,919 --> 00:11:31,919
Can't be kept.

189
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,080
Bro, you're so skinny.

190
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,559
You're not much different.

191
00:12:05,399 --> 00:12:06,399
Come here.

192
00:12:07,399 --> 00:12:08,639
Who are you ordering around?

193
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:10,959
My brother works so hard for you.

194
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,360
I have to give him a good massage.

195
00:12:15,799 --> 00:12:17,119
Aren't you going to do something?

196
00:12:17,559 --> 00:12:19,200
He's the boss in our house.

197
00:12:58,399 --> 00:12:59,399
It's too hot.

198
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,119
Why is it so hot?

199
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:03,158
With soup dumplings, you
have to drink the soup first.

200
00:13:03,159 --> 00:13:04,000
Here, quick.

201
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:04,600
Let me blow on it for you.

202
00:13:04,879 --> 00:13:05,879
Xiao Chen.

203
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,120
This photo

204
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,159
is the only proof

205
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:49,000
of the happy life we had.

206
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:55,480
I'm going to the bathroom.

207
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,520
How was I supposed to know they were here?

208
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,119
They're gone now.

209
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:19,720
Let's continue.

210
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,119
Continue? Yeah, right.

211
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:21,440
Get lost.

212
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:23,200
You're sleeping on the couch tonight.

213
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:48,600
What's wrong?

214
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:49,720
You back with us?

215
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,440
My brother isn't usually like this.

216
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:53,679
What's the big deal?

217
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:54,840
We're adults.

218
00:16:54,879 --> 00:16:56,119
Just think of it as having fun.

219
00:16:58,240 --> 00:17:00,799
This hot spring is pretty tasty.

220
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:04,680
What are you talking about?

221
00:17:23,846 --> 00:17:25,366
So you're just going to flirt and run?

222
00:20:24,839 --> 00:20:25,240
Big bro.

223
00:20:25,359 --> 00:20:25,880
Little bro.

224
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:26,640
Big bro.

225
00:20:26,839 --> 00:20:27,400
Little bro.

226
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,160
Big bro.

227
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:28,759
Little bro.

228
00:20:28,759 --> 00:20:29,720
Big bro.

229
00:20:29,720 --> 00:20:30,559
Little bro.

230
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:31,279
Big bro.

231
00:20:31,279 --> 00:20:32,039
Little bro.

232
00:20:32,279 --> 00:20:32,839
Little bro.

233
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:34,199
Big bro.

234
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,000
Little bro.

235
00:20:35,119 --> 00:20:36,119
Big bro.

236
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,200
Little bro.

237
00:20:38,459 --> 00:20:39,060
Let's go.

238
00:20:39,085 --> 00:20:39,590
Big bro.

239
00:20:39,951 --> 00:20:40,592
Little bro.

240
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:41,640
Big bro.

241
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,240
Little bro.

242
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,240
Go.

243
00:20:45,279 --> 00:20:46,279
Get in the car.

244
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:47,759
Don't look.

245
00:20:48,079 --> 00:20:49,079
Little bro.

246
00:20:49,079 --> 00:20:50,079
Big bro.

247
00:20:50,839 --> 00:20:51,839
Little bro.

248
00:20:53,079 --> 00:20:54,079
Big bro.

249
00:20:54,279 --> 00:20:55,319
My debut is next month.

250
00:20:55,393 --> 00:20:56,153
You have to come.

251
00:20:56,359 --> 00:20:57,000
I'll definitely be there.

252
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,000
You promised me.

253
00:20:59,200 --> 00:20:59,920
Qin Lang.

254
00:21:00,119 --> 00:21:01,200
Driver, go.

255
00:21:01,559 --> 00:21:02,559
Little bro.

256
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,000
Big bro.

257
00:21:04,119 --> 00:21:04,839
Yichen.

258
00:21:04,839 --> 00:21:05,440
Big bro.

259
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:06,440
Yi-chen.

260
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,079
Big bro.

261
00:21:07,079 --> 00:21:08,079
Yi-chen.

262
00:21:08,119 --> 00:21:09,119
Come back.

263
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:11,039
Yi-chen.

264
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:13,440
Does your little brother
have separation anxiety?

265
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,000
What separation anxiety?

266
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,118
He's just a clingy kid.

267
00:21:17,119 --> 00:21:18,799
Does someone in their
twenties still count as a kid?

268
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,799
In my eyes, he'll always be a kid.

269
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:25,440
So if your brother and I
both fell into the ocean,

270
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:27,240
who would you save first?

271
00:21:27,559 --> 00:21:28,559
I'd save my brother.

272
00:21:30,279 --> 00:21:32,640
Because you can swim a
thousand meters in one breath,

273
00:21:32,839 --> 00:21:34,920
but my brother would
sink straight to the bottom.

274
00:21:38,279 --> 00:21:42,118
We're going home. Right now.

275
00:21:42,119 --> 00:21:45,720
Why are we going home so early?

276
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,000
You just said you'd
save your brother first.

277
00:21:48,559 --> 00:21:52,720
Why do you think we're going home?

278
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:55,400
Little bro.

279
00:21:55,799 --> 00:21:56,799
Little bro.

280
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,240
Little bro.

281
00:21:58,680 --> 00:21:59,759
Little bro.

282
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,839
Little bro.

283
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,279
Little bro.

284
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:07,160
Little bro.

285
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:10,680
Okay, fine.

286
00:22:10,839 --> 00:22:12,358
If you're coming, make
up your minds quickly.

287
00:22:12,359 --> 00:22:13,359
Alright.

288
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:17,119
After you.

289
00:22:17,319 --> 00:22:18,319
Okay.

290
00:22:33,119 --> 00:22:34,119
You're back.

291
00:22:35,380 --> 00:22:36,380
Yi-chen.

292
00:22:37,413 --> 00:22:38,413
Yi-chen.

293
00:22:51,519 --> 00:22:52,999
I called you. Why didn't you pick up?

294
00:22:55,319 --> 00:22:56,319
I didn't hear it.

295
00:22:58,039 --> 00:22:58,799
You must be hungry.

296
00:22:58,799 --> 00:22:59,799
Come and eat.

297
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,616
I made something special for you tonight.

298
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:03,000
Your favorite, braised pork belly.

299
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:08,080
Since when do I like braised pork belly?

300
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,240
Are you in a bad mood?

301
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:13,599
What's wrong?

302
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,240
Nothing's wrong.

303
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,759
It's just that...

304
00:23:20,359 --> 00:23:22,279
I don't really like braised pork belly.

305
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:26,200
What did braised pork belly ever do to you?

306
00:23:33,079 --> 00:23:34,079
It's true.

307
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:38,519
I don't think I ever told you

308
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:40,199
that I like this dish.

309
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:42,400
Ever since we got together,

310
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:44,240
you've been brainwashing me,

311
00:23:44,559 --> 00:23:47,240
telling me how delicious
braised pork belly is.

312
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:48,359
And then every day,

313
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:50,079
you'd find a new way to make it for me.

314
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:53,558
And this dish today,

315
00:23:53,559 --> 00:23:54,319
this soup,

316
00:23:54,320 --> 00:23:56,199
I don't like this stir-fried shrimp either.

317
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:57,480
I've never liked it.

318
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:02,759
You're angry just because of this?

319
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:07,519
What's wrong with "this"?

320
00:24:08,279 --> 00:24:09,160
As for me,

321
00:24:09,161 --> 00:24:10,759
I used to love spicy food.

322
00:24:10,976 --> 00:24:12,375
But after getting together with you,

323
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,279
have things been good?

324
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:14,838
I have to eat bland food every day.

325
00:24:14,839 --> 00:24:16,038
Our lifestyles

326
00:24:16,039 --> 00:24:17,680
are completely different.

327
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,919
It's always either you giving in to me

328
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:21,079
or me giving in to you.

329
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:24,440
I've had enough.

330
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,520
I want to break up with you.

331
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:32,440
Cheng Yi-chen.

332
00:24:41,720 --> 00:24:42,559
Breaking up

333
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:44,240
is not something you can just say lightly.

334
00:24:44,559 --> 00:24:46,000
Haven't I told you before?

335
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:48,320
No matter what happens between us,

336
00:24:49,519 --> 00:24:51,199
don't ever bring up breaking up so easily.

337
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:53,079
I'm not saying it lightly.

338
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:55,720
I'm being very serious.

339
00:24:56,119 --> 00:24:57,199
Just because of a few dishes?

340
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:58,200
Yes.

341
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,000
Just because of these few dishes.

342
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,400
I don't want to fight with you.

343
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:12,200
I know.

344
00:25:12,759 --> 00:25:13,919
You must have another reason.

345
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:17,600
If you don't want to talk
about it, I won't force you.

346
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:19,960
But, Yi-chen,

347
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:22,279
you need to know that some things,

348
00:25:22,279 --> 00:25:23,200
no matter how angry you are,

349
00:25:23,201 --> 00:25:24,599
should never be said so easily.

350
00:25:31,319 --> 00:25:33,039
You should calm down and think things over.

351
00:25:33,559 --> 00:25:34,879
I happen to have a business trip.

352
00:25:45,799 --> 00:25:46,839
When I get back,

353
00:25:48,319 --> 00:25:50,079
if you still insist on breaking up,

354
00:25:52,119 --> 00:25:53,119
I'll let you go.

355
00:26:29,222 --> 00:26:30,409
[Mom]

356
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:37,799
Qin Lang.

357
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:39,640
So, how was that girl today?

358
00:26:40,839 --> 00:26:41,839
Mom.

359
00:26:42,039 --> 00:26:43,039
I told you,

360
00:26:43,839 --> 00:26:45,359
I don't want to get married right now.

361
00:27:01,759 --> 00:27:02,759
Xiao Chen.

362
00:27:03,319 --> 00:27:04,639
Want to go out and have some fun?

363
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:06,880
Sure!

364
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,480
So where do you want to go?

365
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:13,559
How about Xicheng?

366
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:19,960
Didn't we already agree
with Yi-chen last time?

367
00:27:20,333 --> 00:27:22,440
We're going to his show this Saturday.

368
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:24,200
You can't go back on your word.

369
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,440
Right?

370
00:27:26,559 --> 00:27:28,160
Didn't you just see your brother?

371
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,838
Some stupid band.

372
00:27:29,839 --> 00:27:31,319
You can go see them anytime you want.

373
00:27:31,599 --> 00:27:32,720
We finally get a break.

374
00:27:33,359 --> 00:27:34,839
Just for one weekend.

375
00:27:36,079 --> 00:27:37,279
Let's just go this once.

376
00:27:37,599 --> 00:27:39,839
I promise I'll go with you
wherever you want after this.

377
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:45,079
Also,

378
00:27:45,920 --> 00:27:46,920
the reunion.

379
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,640
What reunion?

380
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:52,480
My college reunion is this Saturday night.

381
00:27:52,599 --> 00:27:53,959
Your college reunion?

382
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:55,358
What's that got to do with me?

383
00:27:55,359 --> 00:27:56,359
Why would I go there?

384
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,480
They said

385
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:01,000
we could bring a plus-one.

386
00:28:02,039 --> 00:28:03,720
A plus-one?

387
00:28:05,599 --> 00:28:07,000
I told them

388
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:10,160
I was bringing my best friend.

389
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:12,599
Go by yourself.

390
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:13,839
Who's your friend?

391
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:21,160
One step at a time.

392
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:24,680
I'm not going.

393
00:28:27,480 --> 00:28:28,840
If you want to go, go by yourself.

394
00:28:46,799 --> 00:28:47,799
Chou Cheng.

395
00:28:48,759 --> 00:28:50,640
I have some personal
business this Saturday,

396
00:28:51,319 --> 00:28:53,039
so don't schedule any other work for me.

397
00:29:03,319 --> 00:29:04,319
Yi-chen.

398
00:29:05,599 --> 00:29:06,240
Big bro.

399
00:29:06,599 --> 00:29:07,599
You're finally here.

400
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:12,759
You're here too.

401
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:15,400
Where's Qin Lang?

402
00:29:15,401 --> 00:29:16,479
I bought a lot of groceries for you guys.

403
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:17,640
I was going to cook for you.

404
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,440
Who knows where he went?

405
00:29:20,079 --> 00:29:21,079
Did you two fight?

406
00:29:21,559 --> 00:29:23,038
I did not fight with him.

407
00:29:23,039 --> 00:29:24,319
He's such a control freak.

408
00:29:24,799 --> 00:29:25,959
He has to control everything.

409
00:29:26,359 --> 00:29:27,640
With your personality,

410
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:29,176
someone needs to keep you in line.

411
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,319
What's it to you?

412
00:29:31,359 --> 00:29:33,039
You think you're any better than him?

413
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:33,960
Let me tell you something.

414
00:29:34,119 --> 00:29:35,400
If you dare bully my brother,

415
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:36,720
I'll get someone to beat you up.

416
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:38,200
What do you mean, bully?

417
00:29:38,599 --> 00:29:39,640
Like this?

418
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:08,879
Cheng Yichen is here.

419
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:09,960
Yichen is here.

420
00:31:11,359 --> 00:31:12,616
We haven't seen each
other since graduation.

421
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,720
And this is?

422
00:31:14,079 --> 00:31:15,278
This is my good friend, Lu Feng.

423
00:31:15,279 --> 00:31:16,936
He's just been visiting
Xicheng for the past few days.

424
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,319
Come on, come on in.

425
00:31:18,559 --> 00:31:19,999
Cheng Yichen, honestly.

426
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:21,278
This is a couples' gathering.

427
00:31:21,279 --> 00:31:22,439
Not a matchmaking party.

428
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,440
Have a seat.

429
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,480
I mean, you...

430
00:31:24,481 --> 00:31:25,679
It's one thing not to have a girlfriend,

431
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:27,480
but to bring a handsome
guy as your stand-in?

432
00:31:28,119 --> 00:31:29,880
Well, I'm not as handsome and rich as you.

433
00:31:29,920 --> 00:31:31,318
Oh, stop pretending.

434
00:31:31,319 --> 00:31:32,959
Everyone here knows.

435
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:34,118
Back in our department,

436
00:31:34,119 --> 00:31:36,079
how many girls had a crush on you.

437
00:31:36,119 --> 00:31:37,359
That's right!

438
00:31:38,559 --> 00:31:39,559
For real?

439
00:31:39,839 --> 00:31:40,839
You really don't know?

440
00:31:41,079 --> 00:31:42,559
You were our department's heartthrob.

441
00:31:42,599 --> 00:31:43,680
Did no one ever tell you?

442
00:31:44,079 --> 00:31:44,839
Yeah, seriously.

443
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:46,679
You were handsome and got good grades.

444
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:48,159
And you never paid
any attention to us girls.

445
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,240
You were so cool and aloof.

446
00:31:49,319 --> 00:31:50,039
You know?

447
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:50,880
The more you were like that,

448
00:31:50,881 --> 00:31:52,161
the more interested people were.

449
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:54,320
The girls in our class even had a contest.

450
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:56,518
To see who could get you to
say more than ten sentences.

451
00:31:56,519 --> 00:31:57,480
We all placed bets on it.

452
00:31:57,481 --> 00:31:58,999
I remember that!

453
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,719
So, who won in the end?

454
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:02,039
A dark horse.

455
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:04,519
Do you know who won?

456
00:32:05,599 --> 00:32:07,598
It was actually Zhuo Lan who won.

457
00:32:07,599 --> 00:32:09,640
We all lost a ton of money because of her.

458
00:32:10,279 --> 00:32:11,279
Hello.

459
00:32:12,799 --> 00:32:13,720
Zhuo Lan's here.

460
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:14,480
Come on in.

461
00:32:14,481 --> 00:32:15,558
Yichen is over here.

462
00:32:15,559 --> 00:32:16,440
Zhuo Lan.

463
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:17,200
Come, sit here.

464
00:32:17,201 --> 00:32:18,799
I saved this seat especially for you.

465
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:24,920
Lu Feng.

466
00:32:25,079 --> 00:32:26,518
This is my best friend from college,

467
00:32:26,519 --> 00:32:27,519
Zhuo Lan.

468
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:29,000
Zhuo Lan,

469
00:32:29,680 --> 00:32:31,000
this is my...

470
00:32:31,519 --> 00:32:32,519
good friend, Lu Feng.

471
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:36,679
Come on, what are you
all standing around for?

472
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:38,038
Let's have a drink.

473
00:32:38,039 --> 00:32:39,720
Come on, come on, let's drink. Cheers.

474
00:32:40,279 --> 00:32:41,279
Yichen.

475
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:56,960
Yichen.

476
00:32:57,839 --> 00:32:59,440
Zhuo Lan, what's wrong?

477
00:33:00,319 --> 00:33:01,319
There's something...

478
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,760
I've been keeping it to
myself and haven't told you.

479
00:33:04,319 --> 00:33:06,200
But I feel like I should tell you now.

480
00:33:06,799 --> 00:33:07,799
Go ahead.

481
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:09,480
Yichen.

482
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:10,960
I like you.

483
00:33:12,799 --> 00:33:14,680
Ever since the first
time I saw you in college,

484
00:33:15,079 --> 00:33:16,319
I've liked you.

485
00:33:16,839 --> 00:33:18,319
But I never dared to say it.

486
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:20,440
I was afraid we couldn't
even be friends anymore.

487
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:38,640
But I don't want to have any regrets.

488
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:40,960
Yichen, I'm serious.

489
00:33:43,799 --> 00:33:44,799
So...

490
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:46,759
if you're still single right now...

491
00:33:52,519 --> 00:33:53,519
It's okay.

492
00:33:53,759 --> 00:33:55,639
You don't have to give
me an answer right away.

493
00:34:04,519 --> 00:34:05,519
What are you doing?

494
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:07,200
Nothing.

495
00:34:09,039 --> 00:34:11,920
I can't believe you and
Zhuo Lan were classmates.

496
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:14,760
You know each other?

497
00:34:15,159 --> 00:34:16,479
Back in the States,

498
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:18,119
I had a meal with her and her dad.

499
00:34:19,199 --> 00:34:20,919
Her dad is the richest man in Qicheng.

500
00:34:20,920 --> 00:34:21,920
Zhuo Fei.

501
00:34:22,199 --> 00:34:23,199
The rich...

502
00:34:23,599 --> 00:34:24,599
Richest man?

503
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:32,760
Didn't I tell you?

504
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,078
No work scheduled for today.

505
00:34:34,079 --> 00:34:34,639
Bye.

506
00:34:34,639 --> 00:34:35,639
I'm heading out.

507
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:36,960
I got it.

508
00:34:37,039 --> 00:34:38,078
Get the documents ready.

509
00:34:38,079 --> 00:34:39,256
I'll take care of it tomorrow.

510
00:34:39,280 --> 00:34:40,280
Yichen.

511
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:42,679
I'm leaving.

512
00:34:44,800 --> 00:34:45,800
Bye.

513
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:47,360
Bye.

514
00:34:57,599 --> 00:34:58,559
Maybe we should head back first.

515
00:34:58,599 --> 00:35:00,480
No, I'm fine.

516
00:35:00,679 --> 00:35:02,079
Come on, let's go inside.

517
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:06,360
Qin Lang.

518
00:35:07,599 --> 00:35:09,000
Why are you sitting out here?

519
00:35:11,159 --> 00:35:12,759
I'm afraid he'll be upset if he sees me.

520
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:14,960
Why would he be?

521
00:35:15,159 --> 00:35:16,880
I know Cheng Yi-chen's personality.

522
00:35:18,159 --> 00:35:19,559
When you two are together,

523
00:35:19,599 --> 00:35:21,239
there's bound to be some friction.

524
00:35:21,559 --> 00:35:24,159
But, you just have to be patient with him.

525
00:35:25,239 --> 00:35:26,239
He's great.

526
00:35:26,639 --> 00:35:27,639
It's my fault.

527
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:30,480
You must have done something shady.

528
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:31,880
And he found out.

529
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:38,920
I didn't.

530
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,400
Want one?

531
00:36:37,519 --> 00:36:38,840
Let them sort it out themselves.

532
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,560
It's obvious your brother is acting up.

533
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:44,960
Right now, let's solve
the problem between us.

534
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:46,679
What problem do we have?

535
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,360
A big one.

536
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:53,800
It was my fault.

537
00:36:54,039 --> 00:36:55,759
I should have been clear with you that day.

538
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:57,440
That day,

539
00:36:57,880 --> 00:36:59,319
did you see me with a woman?

540
00:36:59,320 --> 00:37:00,320
Together?

541
00:37:02,199 --> 00:37:04,118
She was a blind date
my family set me up with.

542
00:37:04,119 --> 00:37:05,119
Let me finish.

543
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:05,880
We met up...

544
00:37:05,881 --> 00:37:07,440
just to appease our families.

545
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:08,839
She knows my situation.

546
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:10,240
And she has someone she loves, too.

547
00:37:13,599 --> 00:37:15,719
I didn't tell you because
it was already resolved.

548
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,760
I didn't want you to overthink it.

549
00:37:18,519 --> 00:37:19,519
So what?

550
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:22,078
In the end, you're still
going to marry a woman.

551
00:37:22,079 --> 00:37:22,760
I won't.

552
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:23,840
You won't?

553
00:37:24,159 --> 00:37:25,159
What about your parents?

554
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:26,839
You might be able to
brush them off this time,

555
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:27,840
but what about the next?

556
00:37:28,599 --> 00:37:29,599
Cheng Yi-chen.

557
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,198
I'm an adult.

558
00:37:32,199 --> 00:37:33,920
I can be responsible for my own life.

559
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:36,480
As long as you don't break up with me,

560
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:38,239
we will never be apart.

561
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:46,840
Cheng Yi-chen.

562
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:49,239
Try to trust me.

563
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:51,000
Okay?

564
00:38:34,239 --> 00:38:35,000
Lu Feng.

565
00:38:35,001 --> 00:38:36,320
I'll ask you one last time.

566
00:38:36,519 --> 00:38:39,639
Are you really going to give up
everything you have now for Cheng Yichen?

567
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:42,080
I've already made my decision.

568
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,519
Does he know about this?

569
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:48,479
Aren't you afraid it'll be like back then,

570
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:50,519
a one-sided decision on your part?

571
00:38:58,119 --> 00:39:00,880
He's been waiting for
me all these years, too.

572
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:13,919
The agreement has to be
signed back in the States.

573
00:39:13,920 --> 00:39:15,159
You still have a few days.

574
00:39:15,599 --> 00:39:16,719
Think it over.

575
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:34,960
You're back.

576
00:39:36,039 --> 00:39:37,199
Why so many things?

577
00:39:37,679 --> 00:39:40,280
These are New Year's goods for the family.

578
00:39:42,679 --> 00:39:44,039
Shouldn't you...

579
00:39:45,079 --> 00:39:46,559
be heading back to the States, too?

580
00:39:51,039 --> 00:39:52,079
I don't want to go back.

581
00:39:52,679 --> 00:39:53,679
Why not?

582
00:39:56,079 --> 00:39:58,759
Every time I go back,
they rush me to get married.

583
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:01,440
And then it's just endless arguing.

584
00:40:02,159 --> 00:40:03,320
I don't want to leave you.

585
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:06,639
I don't want to leave you either.

586
00:40:07,519 --> 00:40:09,679
But the problem has
to be solved eventually.

587
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:11,559
I think...

588
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:13,800
the only way right now...

589
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,480
is to stall.

590
00:40:16,159 --> 00:40:17,159
Stall?

591
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:20,480
Just keep stalling.

592
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:22,519
As the years go by,

593
00:40:22,840 --> 00:40:24,159
after a while,

594
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:25,760
they'll probably stop bothering us.

595
00:40:26,599 --> 00:40:27,599
And you,

596
00:40:28,159 --> 00:40:30,280
don't be on such bad
terms with your family, either.

597
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,519
We're doing great right now.

598
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:34,320
There's no need to complicate things.

599
00:40:36,519 --> 00:40:37,880
You don't know them.

600
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:43,000
Xiao Chen.

601
00:40:45,039 --> 00:40:47,559
My dad left me a will.
